From 41c9cfdc153414afa9b81ca56b8684d3e93076b1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Pppery <mapreader@olum.org>
Date: Mon, 5 Jan 2026 13:35:32 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 18/50] Fix pluralization errors in `arc anoid`

Summary: Why is this here? Why am I doing this? I have no idea. Anyway, let's have some fun.

Test Plan:
Play 'arc anoid' and immediately press ESC twice:

> You destroyed 0 blocks out of 84 with 0 deaths.

Play again, destroy 1 block, and immediately press ESC twice:

> You destroyed 1 block out of 84 with 0 deaths.

Play again, destroy 2 blocks, and immediately press ESC twice:

> You destroyed 2 blocks out of 84 with 0 death.

See that "block" VS "blocks" and it makes sense.

Die one time, and press ESC twice, to see the singular "death":

> You destroyed 1 block out of 84 with 1 death.

Everything makes sense.

Reviewers: O1 Blessed Committers, valerio.bozzolan

Reviewed By: O1 Blessed Committers, valerio.bozzolan

Subscribers: mainframe98, tobiaswiese, valerio.bozzolan, Matthew, Cigaryno

Differential Revision: https://we.phorge.it/D26660
---
 support/arcanoid/arcanoid.py | 8 ++++++--
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/support/arcanoid/arcanoid.py b/support/arcanoid/arcanoid.py
index 6d99d5e01a51..561e90d86564 100755
--- a/support/arcanoid/arcanoid.py
+++ b/support/arcanoid/arcanoid.py
@@ -227,9 +227,13 @@ def main(stdscr):
         status.refresh()
         time.sleep(0.05)
 
+def plural(n):
+    return '' if n == 1 else 's'
+
 try:
     curses.wrapper(main)
-    print ('You destroyed %s blocks out of %s with %s deaths.' %
-        (Block.killed, Block.total, Ball.killed))
+    print ('You destroyed %s block%s out of %s with %s death%s.' %
+        (Block.killed, plural(Block.killed), Block.total,
+         Ball.killed, plural(Ball.killed)))
 except PowerOverwhelmingException as e:
     print (e)
